# logseq/.gitattributes
# ──────────────────────
# Declares the logseq-merge custom merge driver for Logseq source files.
#
# The driver must be registered in .git/config before it activates.
# Register it once per clone with:
#
#   ant -f ../build.xml register-merge-driver
#
# What the driver does when git encounters a conflict in a matched file:
#   1. Calls: ant -f build.xml resolve-conflicts
#   2. Ant reads the conflict-strategy from logseq/deploy.xml
#   3. Applies git checkout --ours / --theirs accordingly
#   4. Stages and commits the resolution
#
# recursive=binary prevents git from re-invoking the driver recursively
# when resolving a three-way merge; the Ant target handles it atomically.
#
# Patterns
# ─────────
# *.md   — all Logseq page and journal markdown files
# *.edn  — Logseq config files (config.edn, graphs-txid.edn, whiteboards)

*.md    merge=logseq-merge
*.edn   merge=logseq-merge
